ay\n|Recurring role (season 3); main role (seasons 4\u20135); 23 episodes\n|-\n|2013\n|''Rewind''\n|Jessica Knox\n|Television movie\n|-\n|2013\n|''{{sortname|The|Golden Ticket|nolink=1}}''\n|Andrea\n|Short\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Degrassi: The Next Generation]]''\n|Meredith Fox\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Gangland Undercover]]''\n|Suzanna \n|Main role\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Damien (TV series)|Damien]]''\n|Veronica Selvaggio\n|Recurring role, 6 episodes\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]''\n|Lisa Jordan \n|4 episodes\n|-\n|2016\u2013present\n|''[[Wynonna Earp (TV series)|Wynonna Earp]]''\n|Wynonna Earp\n|Lead role\n|-\n|2016\u2013present\n|''[[Letterkenny (TV series)|Letterkenny]]''\n|Mrs. McMurray\n|10 episodes\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Frankie Drake Mysteries]]''\n|Jenny Shaw\n|Episode: \"Ties that Bind\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Bad Blood (TV series)|Bad Blood]]''\n|Valentina Cosoleto\n|Main role (season 2)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://about.rogers.com/2018/05/28/bad-blood-welcomes-new-blood-season-2-city-original-series/ |title=Bad Blood Welcomes New Blood for Season 2 of the City Original Series |date=May 28, 2018 |publisher=Rogers Media |accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Nominated Work\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" | {{Abbr|Refs|References}}\n|-\n| 2017\n| E! Awards\n| Girl on Top\n| ''[[Wynonna Earp (TV series)|Wynonna Earp]]''\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | <ref>{{cite web|author=Lauren Piester|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/877237/girl-on-top-2017-vote-in-the-final-round-now|title=Girl on Top 2017: Vote in the Final Round Now|work=E! Online|date=September 1, 2017|access-date=2017-09-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[Canadian Screen Awards]]\n| Audience Choice Award\n| Herself\n| {{Won|place=Bronze|Top 3}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | <ref>{{cite web|author=Nootvanlis|