ige Scrofano''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] actress. She is known for playing the roles of Rebecca on the [[CBC Television|CBC]] [[dramedy]] series ''[[Being Erica]]'', October on the [[Showcase (Canadian TV channel)|Showcase]] comedy [[mockumentary]] series ''[[Pure Pwnage]]'', and Tia on the [[CTV Television Network]] fantasy drama series ''[[The Listener (TV series)|The Listener]]''.<ref>{{cite news |author=Andrew Ryan |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/seven-days-of-television-may-26-to-june-1/article18819671/ |title=Seven Days of Television: May 26 to June 1 [1 of 7] |work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |date=May 26, 2014 |accessdate=2016-05-29}}</ref> Scrofano has played the lead role on [[Syfy]]'s modern Western drama ''[[Wynonna Earp (TV series)|Wynonna Earp]]'' since 2016.<ref>{{cite news |author=Lesley Goldberg |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/syfy-acquires-comic-book-adaptation-810544 |title=Syfy Acquires Comic Book Adaptation 'Wynonna Earp' |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 22, 2015 |accessdate=2016-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Nellie Andreeva |url=https://deadline.com/2015/07/syfy-wynonna-earp-series-cast-melanie-scrofano-1201483399/ |title=Syfy Acquires \u2018Wynonna Earp\u2019 Series; Melanie Scrofano To Star |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 22, 2015 |accessdate=2016-05-29}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nScrofano grew up in [[Ottawa]], Ontario.<ref>{{cite news |author=Eric Volmers |url=https://calgaryherald.com/entertainment/television/calgary-shot-wynonna-earp-ready-to-action |title=Calgary-shot Wynonna Earp ready for action |work=[[Calgary Herald]] |date=March 31, 2016 |accessdate=2016-05-29 }}</ref> Her father is an engineer and her mother is a government worker. She is of Italian and French-Canadian descent. She began modeling at the age of 13, and picked up acting when her agent began submitting her for acting jobs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.panoramitalia.com/en/arts-culture/music/lives-melanie-scrofano/1283/|title=The many lives of  Melanie Scrofano - Panoram Italia|last=Imagiamedia.ca|website=www.panoramitalia.com|language=en|access-date=2017-08-27}}</ref>\n\nIt was revealed in a July 2017 ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' article that Scrofano was pregnant for the duration of filming the second season of ''[[Wynonna Earp (TV series)|Wynonna Earp]]''. She gave birth to a son in April 2017, shortly after production on the series had wrapped.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/features/wynonna-earp-emily-andras-melanie-scrofano-news-exclusive-1202476757/|title=\u2018Wynonna Earp\u2019 Exclusive: Showrunner Emily Andras and Star Melanie Scrofano Break Down That Big Reveal|author=Maureen Ryan|date=July 8, 2017|work=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://calgaryherald.com/entertainment/television/no-pregnant-pause-expecting-a-baby-didnt-slow-down-wynonna-earp-or-the-actress-playing-her|title=\u2018No pregnant pause: Expecting a baby didn't slow down Wynonna Earp or the actress playing her|author=Eric Volmers|date=August 4, 2017|work=Calgary Herald|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-19}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Baby Blues (2008 film)|Baby Blues]]''\n|Mani White\n|\n|-\n|2009\n|''{{sortname|A|Good Meal|nolink=1}}''\n|Nancy\n|\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Saw VI]]''\n|Gena\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Citizen Gangster]]''\n|Ann Roberts\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''{{sortname|The|Conspiracy|nolink=1}}''\n|Sarah\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''Yeah Rite''\n|Jenny / Zod\n|Short film\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Nurse 3D]]''\n|Rachel Adams\n|\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Wolves (2014 film)|Wolves]]''\n|Gail Timmins\n|<ref>{{cite magazine |author=Dennis Harvey |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-wolves-1201357039/ |title=Film Review: \u2018Wolves\u2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=November 15, 2014 |accessdate=2016-05-29 |quote=That status goes uncontested by Melanie Scrofano as her sister, a comic-relief drunk with a limp.}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[RoboCop (2014 film)|RoboCop]]''\n|Wife of Man with Prosthetics\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''A Sunday Kind of Love''\n|Emma / Death\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''Mangiacake''\n|Tessa\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''Birdland''\n|Merle James\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Ready or Not (2019 film)|Ready or Not]]''\n|Emilie\n|<ref name=\"Mendelson2019\">{{cite news |author=Scott Mendelson |title='Ready Or Not' Review: Movies Like This Are (Hopefully) Why Disney Bought Fox |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/08/14/ready-or-not-review-fox-disney-samara-weaving-andie-macdowell-melanie-scrofano-adam-brody/#13def8f2766b |work=Forbes |date=August 14, 2019 |access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{TableTBA}}\n|''[[The Silencing]]''\n|{{TableTBA}}\n|<ref>{{cite news |author=Amanda N'Duka |title='Wynonna Earp' Star Melanie Scrofano, Zahn McClarnon, Shaun Smyth Board 'The Silencing' |url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/wynonna-earp-melanie-scrofano-zahn-mcclarnon-shaun-smyth-the-silencing-1202606182/ |work=Deadline |date=May 2, 2019 |access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Undressed]]''\n|Isobel\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|''Mob Stories''\n|Menard's Girlfriend\n|Episode: \"Don of St. Leonard\"\n|-\n|2004\n|''[[Naked Josh]]''\n|Marla\n|Episode: \"Family Misgivings\"\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[Beautiful People (U.S. TV series)|Beautiful People]]''\n|Emma Lovren\n|Episodes: \"Best Face Forward\", \"And the Winner Is...\"\n|-\n|2006\u20132007\n|''[[Jeff Ltd.]]''\n|Nathalie\n|4 episodes\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Supernatural (U.S. TV series)|Supernatural]]''\n|Near-Dead Girl\n|Episode: \"[[What Is and What Should Never Be (Supernatural)|What Is and What Should Never Be]]\"\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Anne of Green Gables: A New Beginning]]''\n|Brigitte\n|Television movie\n|-\n|2009\n|''Manson''\n|Leslie Van Houten\n|Television movie\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Kids in the Hall: Death Comes to Town]]''\n|French Girl / Peg Liaro\n|Episode: \"Who Mailed Our Mayor?\"\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Pure Pwnage]]''\n|October\n|Main role\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Covert Affairs]]''\n|Jane / Woman #2\n|Episode: Pilot\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Baxter (TV series)|Baxter]]''\n|Ms. Mansfield\n|3 episodes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Being Erica]]''\n|Rebecca\n|Recurring role, 10 episodes\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Mudpit (TV series)|Mudpit]]''\n|Leah\n|Episode: \"Travellin' Band\"\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Rookie Blue]]''\n|Sophie Lewis\n|Episode: \"The One That Got Away\"\n|-\n|2011\n|''Dave vs Death''\n|Sheila\n|Short\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]''\n|Holly McCord\n|Episode: \"Grounded\"\n|-\n|2011\n|''Stay with Me''\n|Alison\n|Television movie\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Haven (TV series)|Haven]]''\n|Noelle\n|Episodes: \"Magic Hour: Parts 1 & 2\"\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Saving Hope]]''\n|Kym Spencer\n|Episode: \"Contact\"\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Warehouse 13]]''\n|Alice/Kristen\n|Episode: \"Fractures\"\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Heartland (Canadian TV series)|Heartland]]''\n|Hayley Powers\n|Episode: \"Life Is a Highway\"\n|-\n|2012\u20132014\n|''{{sortname|The|Listener|The Listener (TV series)}}''\n|Tia Tremblay\n|Recurring role (season 3); main role (seasons 4\u20135); 23 episodes\n|-\n|2013\n|''Rewind''\n|Jessica Knox\n|Television movie\n|-\n|2013\n|''{{sortname|The|Golden Ticket|nolink=1}}''\n|Andrea\n|Short\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Degrassi: The Next Generation]]''\n|Meredith Fox\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Gangland Undercover]]''\n|Suzanna \n|Main role\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Damien (TV series)|Damien]]''\n|Veronica Selvaggio\n|Recurring role, 6 episodes\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]''\n|Lisa Jordan \n|4 episodes\n|-\n|2016\u2013present\n|''[[Wynonna Earp (TV series)|Wynonna Earp]]''\n|Wynonna Earp\n|Lead role\n|-\n|2016\u2013present\n|''[[Letterkenny (TV series)|Letterkenny]]''\n|Mrs. McMurray\n|10 episodes\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Frankie Drake Mysteries]]''\n|Jenny Shaw\n|Episode: \"Ties that Bind\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Bad Blood (TV series)|Bad Blood]]''\n|Valentina Cosoleto\n|Main role (season 2)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://about.rogers.com/2018/05/28/bad-blood-welcomes-new-blood-season-2-city-original-series/ |title=Bad Blood Welcomes New Blood for Season 2 of the City Original Series |date=May 28, 2018 |publisher=Rogers Media |accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Nominated Work\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" | {{Abbr|Refs|References}}\n|-\n| 2017\n| E! Awards\n| Girl on Top\n| ''[[Wynonna Earp (TV series)|Wynonna Earp]]''\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | <ref>{{cite web|author=Lauren Piester|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/877237/girl-on-top-2017-vote-in-the-final-round-now|title=Girl on Top 2017: Vote in the Final Round Now|work=E! Online|date=September 1, 2017|access-date=2017-09-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[Canadian Screen Awards]]\n| Audience Choice Award\n| Herself\n| {{Won|place=Bronze|Top 3}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | <ref>{{cite web|author=Nootvanlis|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wV3QJ6uk0iQ|title=Elise Bauman winning the Audience Choice Award at the 2018 Canadian Screen Awards|work=Youtube|date=March 11, 2018|access-date=2018-03-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| Canadian Screen Awards\n| [[Canadian Screen Award for Best Actress in a Continuing Leading Dramatic Role|Best Lead Actress, Drama Series]]\n| ''Wynonna Earp''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | <ref name=\"Mrazek2019\">{{cite news |author=Sarah-Ann Mrazek |title=The 2019 Canadian Screen Awards Nominees Have Been Announced |url=https://fashionmagazine.com/culture/2019-canadian-screen-awards-nominees/ |work=[[Fashion (magazine)|Fashion]] |date=February 7, 2019 |access-date=2019-09-12}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist