inn Spinsanity''. Relocated from Six Flags AstroWorld.\n|-\n|Tri-Star\n|[[Spanish City]]\n|\n|\n|1984\n|{{no|1984}}\n|Relocated from [[Pleasureland Southport]].\n|-\n|Scorpion\n|Talley Amusements, Inc. (Showman)\n|{{flagicon|USA}} United States\n|Tivoli\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://talleyamusements.com/ride-details.asp?rideid=8|title=Talley Amusements - Scorpion|last=www.mwdwebdesign.com|first=Matt's Web Design-|website=Talley Amusements|language=en|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n|-\n|Calgary Stampede\n|[[Thorpe Park]]\n|{{flagicon|UK}} United Kingdom\n|\n|1993\n|{{no|2003}}\n|\n|-\n|Troika\n|[[Toshimaen]]\n|{{flagicon|Japan}} Japan\n|\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|\n|-\n|Mustang Runner\n|[[Worlds of Fun]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} United States\n|HUSS\n|2017\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|<ref>[https://www.worldsoffun.com/play/rides/mustang-runner Mustang Runner - Worlds of Fun Website]</ref>\n|-\n|Dancing Queen\n|Unknown - German Showman\n|{{flagicon|Germany}} Germany\n|\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|Traveling version in Germany.\n|}\n\n\n==See also==\n{{commons category|Troika (ride)}}\n* [[Twist (ride)]]\n\n{{HUSS Park Attractions}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Amusement rides]]\n[[Category:Amusement rides introduced in 1975]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "name_user": "Mullins.170", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTroika Installations:Added serial number for Kings Island's ride unit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Troika_(ride)"}
{"title_page": "John Tufnell", "text_new": "[[File:Langleys, Great Waltham (geograph 3375546).jpg|thumb|Langleys, Great Waltham]]\n'''John Joliffe Tufnell'''  (1720\u20131794), was a British politician who sat in the [[House of Commons]] from 1754 to 1761.\n \nTufnell was the son of [[Samuel Tufnell]] MP of Monken Hadley, Hertfordshire and Langleys, Essex and his wife  Elizabeth Cressener, daughter of George Cressener of Earl's Colne, Essex and was born on 27 June 1720. He entered [[Middle Temple]]  in 1737 and [[Corpus Christi, Cambridge]] in 1738. He married Anna Meeke, daughter of William Meeke of Northallerton, Yorkshire on 2 April 1748.<ref name = HOP>{{cite web| url = http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1754-1790/member/tufnell-john-jolliffe-1720-94| title= TUFNELL, John Jolliffe (1720-94), of Langleys, Essex| publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 9 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nTufnell was elected as [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Beverley (UK Parliament constituency)|Beverley]] in a contest in the [[1754 British general election|1754 general election]]. Little is known of his contribution in parliament. He was listed under the heading \u201ccountry gentlemen\u201d and was counted as a Government supporter. He did not stand in 1761 when his brother [[George Tufnell|George]] took over the seat.<ref name = HOP/>\n\nTufnell succeeded his father on 28 December 1758, inheriting Langleys in Great Waltham, Essex. He became one of the richest commoners in England, renting out property in Essex and the north. He died on 23 September 1794.<ref name = HOP/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{s-bef\n | before  = [[Charles Pelham (died 1763)|Charles Pelham]]\n | before2 = [[Sir William Codrington, 2nd Baronet|Sir William Codrington, Bt]]\n}}\n{{s-title\n | title = [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Beverley (UK Parliament constituency)|Beverley]]\n | years = [[1754 British general election|1754]]\u2013[[1761 British general election|1761]]\n | with  =  [[Sir William Codrington, 2nd Baronet|Sir William Codrington, Bt]]\n  \n}}\n{{s-aft\n | after  = [[Michael Newton (died 1803)|Michael Newton]]\n | after2 = [[George Tufnell]]\n}}\n\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tufnell, John Joliffe}}\n[[Category:1720 births]]\n[[Category:1794 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1754\u20131761]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Langleys, Great Waltham (geograph 3375546).jpg|thumb|Langleys, Great Waltham]]\n'''John Joliffe Tufnell'''  (1720\u20131794), was a British politician who sat in the [[House of Commons]] from 1754 to 1761.\n \nTufnell was the son of [[Samuel Tufnell]] MP of Monken Hadley, Hertfordshire and Langleys, Essex and his wife  Elizabeth Cressener, daughter of George Cressener of Earl\u2019s Colne, Essex and was born on 27 June 1720. He entered [[Middle Temple]]  in 1737 and [[Corpus Christi, Cambridge]] in 1738. He married Anna Meeke, daughter of William Meeke of Northallerton, Yorkshire on 2 April 1748.<ref name = HOP>{{cite web| url = http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1754-1790/member/tufnell-john-jolliffe-1720-94| title= TUFNELL, John Jolliffe (1720-94), of Langleys, Essex| publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 9 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nTufnell was elected as [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Beverley (UK Parliament constituency)|Beverley]] in a contest in the [[1754 British general election|1754 general election]]. Little is known of his contribution in parliament. He was listed under the heading \u201ccountry gentlemen\u201d and was counted as a Government supporter. He did not stand in 1761 when his brother [[George Tufnell|George]] took over the seat.<ref name = HOP/>\n\nTufnell succeeded his father on 28 December 1758, inheriting Langleys in Great Waltham, Essex. He became one of the richest commoners in England, renting out property in Essex and the north. He died on 23 September 1794.<ref name = HOP/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{s-bef\n | before  = [[Charles Pelham (died 1763)|Charles Pelham]]\n | before2 = [[Sir William Codrington, 2nd Baronet|Sir William Codrington, Bt]]\n}}\n{{s-title\n | title = [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Beverley (UK Parliament constituency)|Beverley]]\n | years = [[1754 British general election|1754]]\u2013[[1761 British general election|1761]]\n | with  =  [[Sir William Codrington, 2nd Baronet|Sir William Codrington, Bt]]\n  \n}}\n{{s-aft\n | after  = [[Michael Newton (died 1803)|Michael Newton]]\n | after2 = [[George Tufnell]]\n}}\n\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tufnell, John Joliffe}}\n[[Category:1720 births]]\n[[Category:1794 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1754\u20131761]]\n", "name_user": "J947", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Tufnell"}
